      <section eId="sec_CHC-560">
        <num>CHC 560</num>
        <heading>560. Â Provision of services; qualifications of counsel</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-560__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A program designated by the Louisiana Supreme Court shall provide child representation services to each court exercising jurisdiction over abuse and neglect cases in accordance with a plan for service delivery developed by the program and approved by the supreme court.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-560__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Representation of children in child abuse and neglect cases shall comply with the provisions of Part III of Rule J of the Administrative Rules of the Supreme Court, including qualifications of appointed counsel and child attorney standards.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=408235</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
